doctype 5
html
  head
    title=title
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/milligram/1.3.0/milligram.min.css')
  body  
    header
    .container        
      .row          
        .column.column-50.column-offset-25
          h1 Timestamp Microservice
          blockquote
            h2 User stories:
            p 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
            p 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
            p 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.          
          h3 Example usage:
          pre: code=url+'/December%2015,%202015'
          pre: code=url+'/January 1, 2016'
          pre: code=url+'/1450137600'
          h3 Example output:
          pre: code { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }            
    footer
